{"lemma":"صُلْحُ","slug":"صُلْحُ","root":"ص.ل.ح","root_slug":"ص-ل-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ل-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صُلْح","root":"صلح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24712","n24719","n24720"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be righteous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in good or perfect condition"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be honest, to be upright"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to suit, respond, answer the purpose, be adequate","examples":[{"text":"11 Century CE, Wallada bint al-Mustakfi, أنا واللّه أصلح للمعالي\nأَنَا وَ الْلَّهِ أَصْلُحُ لِلْمَعَالِي ، وَأَمْشِي مِشْيَتِي وَأَتِيهُ تِيهَا\nʔanā wa l-llahi ʔaṣluḥu lilmaʕālī , waʔamšī mišyatī waʔatīhu tīhā\nI am, by Allah, adequate for high positions. And am going my way, with pride."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be righteous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in good or perfect condition"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be honest, to be upright"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fix, mend, improve","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reconciliation","examples":[{"text":"وَإِنِ ٱمْرَأَةٌ خَافَتْ مِن بَعْلِهَا نُشُوزًا أَوْ إِعْرَاضًا فَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْهِمَا أَن يُصْلِحَا بَيْنَهُمَا صُلْحًا وَٱلصُّلْحُ خَيْرٌ","english":"And if a woman fears from her husband any inharmony or rebuffing, there is no blame on them if they reconcile. Indeed, reconciliation is good!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peace"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From صَلَحَ (ṣalaḥa, “to be right; to be adequate; to be sound, to be whole etc.”). Possibly influenced by Aramaic סָלַח (sālaḥ, “to forgive”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24712","headword_ar":"صَلَحَ","root":"SlH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, Mgh, Msb,) the well-known form, though omitted in the K, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, K, Msb,) [said by some to be] the more chaste, because agreeable with analogy, (TA,) [but the former is the more common,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuluwHN","text_ar":"صُلُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MA, Mgh, Msb, K * [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aluwH","text_ar":"الصَّلُوح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uluwH","text_ar":"الصُّلُوح"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHN","text_ar":"صَلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * MA, Mgh, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSolaHapN","text_ar":"مَصْلَحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaluHa","text_ar":"صَلُحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, Mgh, Msb, K,) mentioned by Fr, on the authority of his companions, (S, TA,) but said by IDrd to be not well established, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHN","text_ar":"صَلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHapN","text_ar":"صَلَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHiyapN","text_ar":"صَلَاحِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) said of a thing, (S, Mgh, Msb,) and of a man, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good, incorrupt, right, just, righteous, virtuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest; it was"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a good, incorrupt, sound, right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of order; he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, throve; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fsd","text_ar":"فسد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasada","text_ar":"فَسَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasuda","text_ar":"فَسُدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (MA; [and S and A and Mgh and K by implication; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHN","text_ar":"صَلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below;]) in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nyk $d","text_ar":"نيك شد"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstSlH","text_ar":"استصلح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHN","text_ar":"صَلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotiSolaAHN","text_ar":"اِسْتِصْلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nyk $dn","text_ar":"نيك شدن"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KL.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaHato HaAlu fulaAnK","text_ar":"صَلَحَتْ حَالُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of such a one became good, right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^adiymN yaSoluHu liln~aEoli","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَدِيمٌ يَصْلُحُ لِلنَّعْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is leather that is suitable for the sandal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Al$~aYo'u yaSoluHu laka","text_ar":"هٰذَا الشَّىْءُ يَصْلُحُ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This thing is suitable to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet, for thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yaSoluHu liSuHobatika","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يَصْلُحُ لِصُحْبَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is not fit for being thy companion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","MA","Mgh","Msb","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n24719","headword_ar":"صُلْحٌ","root":"SlH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSaAlaHapN","text_ar":"مُصَالَحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, KT,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with the latter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) masc. and fem.; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Peace, reconciliation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agreement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K, KT, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after contention:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the law it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compact to give over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relinquish, contention."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa","text_ar":"وَقَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumaA SuloHN","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمَا صُلْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Peace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reconciliation, took place between them two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxi*a SuloHFA","text_ar":"اُخِذَ صُلْحًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a fortress or the like)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was taken peacefully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by surrender."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  Also That"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of which there has been made a peaceful compact:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which has been taken in the way of peace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A party at peace with others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo lanaA SuloHN","text_ar":"هُمْ لَنَا صُلْحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a party"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at peace with us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And you say also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN SuluwHN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ صُلُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, who are at peace:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the latter word in this case being app. an inf. n. used as an epithet. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","KT","Mgh","K","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n24720","headword_ar":"صَلْحٌ","root":"SlH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}